Title: They don’t fall out
Review_Body: When I was considering buying the AirPods I was apprehensive due to them potentially falling out. I got these to wear while bike riding, shopping, and going to the gym. In order to hear the traffic around me and to avoid being hit by a car, I only wear one AirPod. Today, as I was crossing an intersection at a green light, a woman driving a car ran the red light and hit me. I’m okay (only some broken bones, bruises, cuts, and sprains), but what I am most pleased about is my one AirPod did not fall out! My main concern has been proven to be false, and I was lucky enough to be the one to prove it wrong! Seriously, you should get these. They’re great and they don’t fall out (even if you get hit by a car).

Title: Sound Pretty Good, Fit Not So Much
Review_Body:
The sound quality of the AirPods is pretty decent, as well as the build quality. A nice introduction into the AirPods game. You can say the same for the build quality as well; sturdy and premium feeling. 

That being said, these are definitely not for everyone. The main reason being their fit. I actually had to return them as they would dig into my ears, and not having any padding, it was hard plastic against skin. 

If you can, definitely upgrade to the wireless charger as well, or if you can push your budget a little bit more I would highly recommend the AirPods Pro. I ended up just upgrading to them after the fit issue and I do not even regret spending the additional money. 

Are these good, yes, just double check their fit for you ears.

Title: These don't last
Review_Body: I bought these AirPods on 10/2/20 and on 3/15/21 the right bud stopped working.  At least I bought apple care protection.  Hopefully Apple will replace.  This is my second pair of AirPods since July 2020.  The first pair was AirPod Pros.  I had them engraved.  The buds stopped taking a charge within a month.  I couldn't return for a replacement because I'd had them engraved. (If you have them engraved you have to return them and order another pair from scratch). So I just returned them and ordered a cheaper pair, without the engraving.  I figure if these things are going to be cheap and unreliable, I'm not going to bother engraving the case.

Got a silicone cover with hook to protect the charging case - is recommended - to keep case safe and hook it on belt loop or purse handle. You don't have to remove the cover to charge the case so is very convenient.

Title: YES...do it!!
Review_Body:
I have to admit...I just didn't want to spend the money. I owned a pair of Bose and they were "fine".  However, after purchasing the AirPods I really "heard" the difference in the quality of the Apple product.  BEST purchase I have made for both the quality of sound and the ease of use! 
As an added bonus they maintain their charge life for a long period of time!

Title: Great everyday use headphones!
Review_Body:
As a music enthusiast headphones are probably my most used tech product (aside from my phone) it took me quite some time to jump on board the Airpods band wagon but I have zero regrets. If you are on the fence and debating if it’s worth it read below I have broken it down as simple as possible to tell you why it’s worth all the fuss. 

Design and Comfort: 
Apple’s style is very distinctive and if you have even owned any apple product you know everything they design is slick and easy to carry. They fit anywhere and come in their own little charging case to keep them fully charged. The airpods themselves fit easily within your ears despite the shape of your ear canal. I was a bit hesitant at first if they were good throughout a full work but I have used these while doing a high intensity spinning class and while doing HIIT workouts and they remain safe and secure within my ears without falling out. Aside from the fact that they remain within my ear they also cause no discomfort even during long listening periods. In fact they are so comfortable I use them to talk over the phone in order to be hands free. If you ask me they nailed it. 

Sound Quality:
By far the number one reason you purchase headphones is if the sound quality is worth it. I will tell you the rest of the wireless headphones have some competition because the sound is quite impressive. The bass sounds great without overpowering the song during a workout and gives a crisp sound while listening to podcast. 

Connectivity: 
Apple has made syncing your aipods straight out of the box to your phone the easiest process ever. Simply open the Airpods case next to your phone and select the option on your screen to pair them. 1, 2, 3 and you are good to go. Each time you put an airpod in your ear it automatically connects and plays whatever you are listening to on your phone. In addition to that they also automatically disconnect when you take them off which personally is my favorite feature. It’s so simple you will wonder why isn’t everything as simple as this. 

Final Verdict: 
There are no negative reviews or bad experiences I have had with these. I highly recommend going into the store and taking a peak for yourself but you will not be disappointed with your purchase. They are an everyday for every type of use headphones.

I love classic rock and hip hop / rap so having a pair that produces a good amount of bass is huge for me and these are it ! I bought a pair of beats wireless earbuds and honestly, they trash in sound quality and whose name is on those ? A notorious hip hop producer go figure. 

The free wired earbuds we get with iPhones are far better in the sound department than my beats. Anyway, these are excellent and have done me well thus far. I’ll definitely upgrade to the pro’s at some point. 

Best Buy shipped these super quick in the middle of this pandemic too and I literally had them the day after I ordered. Huge shout out to Best Buy on the lightning fast shipping.

Title: Expensive but flawless performance
Review_Body:
I love these little guys. I am a headphone junkie. I have Bose noise cancelling for travel, Aftershockz for swimming, and these AirPods for all day/ everyday. I keep these in my pocket for phone calls, mostly, and they never fail me. Apple makes for quick connect and they work with my iPad, too. I am able to hear music, podcasts, and phone calls while maintaining awareness of my surroundings. 

Recommend a case for scratch and drop protection. 

This purchase was for my daughter going off to college. I have actually owned my pair for more than six months.

Title: An old standby that just works
Review_Body: I had these for years, and then they died.  I tried a bunch of other options (jabra, MSFT, etc) and ultimately bought another pair of these on a sale, and I'm glad to have them back.  They are not the best audio experience, or filled with amazing features like noise cancelling, but they just work, they fit my ears and I'm totally satisfied.

Title: My everywhere buds

The sound quality is also great for what you get. I can get over 2 hours on a charge, but these buds recharge quickly from the portable recharging case they come in. No wireless recharging with this case, but it can last a few days for me before needing to plug into a wall charger - dependent on usage. These are my third pair, and for the price, they are well worth the cost

Title: Good Sound Quality, But Overpriced.
Review_Body: I really wanted a pair of earbuds, but was unsure about which brand to get. I primarily wanted to use earbuds to talk on the phone, but I was turned off about purchasing airpods because the battery life for phone calls was too short. However, after reading reviews online and talking to a few people who own airpods, I decided to go head and purchase them.  I was pleasantly surprised after getting my airpods.The sound quality is awesome while listening to music and podcasts. I own an android phone and they work perfectly. The sound quality during phone calls is great too. However, the talk time is usually considerably less than the 3 hrs advertised.  To extend my talk time I just use one airpod at a time. This way I can talk all day as long as I keep recharging. In the past, I rarely listened to music on my phone with headphones. However, because the sound quality of the airpods is so great I listen to music, youtube videos, the radio, podcasts and everything else now all day on my phone. Despite the great sound quality, I deducted a star in my rating because of the short battery life for phone calls. I also think that airpods are a bit overpriced for what they do. I purchased mine while on sale so that made things a little better, but even at the reduced price they are still over priced to me. Overall though, I am relatively happy with my purchase.

Title: Good purchase

Title: Incredibly Convenient & Intuitive
Review_Body: It was after making the purchase and using the AirPods for a while that I realized I probably should have acquired them sooner. They paired up with my devices almost immediately, I can be within a moderate distance of said devices and still get uninterrupted sound (something that has improved with the second generation of AirPods) and after a lengthy session with them, I can place them in their charging case and expect them to be fully charged within fifteen minutes. The double tap gestures (play/pause/next) and the use of Siri are seamlessly integrated and it’s great to know that whatever I have playing will instantly pause if I remove the AirPods. Overall, they’ve been great and I’ve actively recommended them since.

Review_Body:
Purchased 12/22/2019

Best Buy could have received them that way. Never dropped, no water damage, it seems to be a manufacturing defected product or maybe a refurbished product. Doesn't look good coming from Apple being sold by Best Buy. I truly expected more of the product as well as the retailer. Truly disappointed.

Title: Good - but - not Great ...
Review_Body: Ok - “back” in the day - I use to work for two of the most recognized high end Stereo Shops in Toronto Canada - Toronto HiFi & The Great Metropolitan Sound Company & we use to sell ubber hi-end audio gear - so - I use to have extremely well tuned ears & when I felt my ears were getting flat - I use to sneak off to Ring Audio - which was SO exclusive - you couldn’t even find the place unless you were referred there. So ... being very old school & having my ears hit that “old” plateau - the one where you can hear the compression of MP3’s & still put up with it - cause frankly @ this “age” in life - you just don’t care - cause you just want to hear the music - ya ... these headphones suck - but - there are SO many other good points “the needs of the many - out weigh the needs of the one” - like the case keeps the buds charged without being plugged in 7-24-365 / the buds sync every-single-time I’ve plugged into my ears - the buds charge once you drop them back into the case - I’ve gone 5 uses @ at least 90mins before I was worried & plugged the case in with the buds in charge mode - sooooooo ya ... the innovative points of being able to use ‘em - when you need ‘em kinda-sorta out weighs the “sonic” experience - there just ok - absolutely not close to live studio or live production - but decent enough - the plug in ear / settle with the contour of your ear is just ok / nothing special - but combine the features & your going to get a decent little pair of head-phones ...

Title: Game changer!
Review_Body: I was hesitant to purchase Apple AirPods at first because of the price. I ended up buying a pair of cheaper wireless earbuds but ultimately didn’t like the way they fit in my ear and hated the sound quality. I figured I would just research and find another pair of cheaper earbuds. After a couple of days with the second pair I realized what a mistake I had made. If I continued purchasing cheaper products, I would end up spending more money over time than I would if I just bought the Apple AirPods in the first place! I’ve always been extremely satisfied with the fit and sound quality of the Apple earbuds that came with my phone and these are even better and wireless.

Title: apple airpods & Logan
Review_Body:
This review is more about the sales/service rep.  Logan was the best sales rep I've encountered in a very very long time. Didn't talk down to me. Answered all my stupid questions with aplomb. Didn't try to upsale.  If I decided to buy in the future, I would definitely seek him out.
The apple airpods (2019) are great as well.  Fit my ears better than the Pro.  They have not fallen out yet & i'm a pretty active person. Sound is great even on calls which was important to me. I would recommend both the Airpods & Logan to family & friends.

Title: Easily one of the best products I’ve purchased
Review_Body: Seriously the best headphones ever. I got an off brand from another store (let’s call is smarget) and I didn’t like the way that they fit in my ears. So the air pods were only like $40 more at that point (I had gotten them on sale) and I love them. So easy to set up and you can wear one ear bud at a time if you need to be able to hear people (I will wear them this at work sometimes so I can talk to others). Some ear pods I know can only be used together if you’re on a call or some such but I’ve had no issue with that at all. Everyone says that they can hear me clearly and it’s great sound quality. Def a NEED for any apple enthusiast. (Or if you’re like me where you’re ocd and EVERYTHING MUST MATCH)

Title: Very convenient and hassle-free technology!
Review_Body:
I've used regular Apple earphones for many years, and the only small issue I had with them was that they tangle very easily.. which is why when I realized I had a lot of points racked up from My Best Buy Visa credit card, I decided to use them towards getting the new Apple Airpods; at first I didn't think they'd be that necessary, but I was convinced to get them anyways. 

I love that they are wireless and have a little protective charging case. They are very easy to connect to your device as well; I've connected them to my iPhone and my Macbook. They are pretty small so they might be easy to lose, if only they had a pinging feature like the Apple Watch does! Overall, I am happy with my purchase!

Title: These AirPods are OK, but Definitely Not Prs
Review_Body:
Apple's AirPods are OK but their battery life, even brand new, is absolutely a joke.  The automatically switching version of the AirPods can't come fast enough as even Bose Noise Cancelling 700 Head Phones don't consistently do this basic function well.

If all you're trying to do is watch movies on your iPad or listen to music off of your iPhone (without being connected to another device at the same time) then these are fine.  If you want to watch movies around your iPhone and be able to answer an incoming call think again.

Title: AirPod review

Title: Some good, some not so good
Review_Body: I have mixed feelings about this product.  I'm a true Apple Kool-Aid drinker, and this is the first time I've ever given less than 5 stars to an Apple product.  First, the good......the quality of the sound is so very, very good.  It has really changed my cell phone experience (NOTE:  I'm a senior with hearing loss).  The bad.....I only get about 4 hours of battery life out of the case.  I run a business from my home that requires me to be on the phone 8 hours+ a day.  Around midday, I need to switch to my Earpods for the rest of the day.  If Apple could do something about the battery life, I'd give it 5 stars.

Title: Great Ear Buds
Review_Body: They're really great.  I travel weekly on my job and my concern was keeping them in my ears while on planes and traversing through airports.  They've been NO PROBLEM in that regard.  They STAY in your ears. Sound is absolutely great.  I guess the ONLY reason I didn't give them a 5 Star Rating is because at times the noisy airplane engine noise on flights often drowns out the quieter songs.  I've tried everything to squeeze more volume from my phone and/or the AirPods but to no avail. I used Jaybird X series prior and I do like the AirPods more.  I just wish they had the same louder volume capability that I had with the Jaybirds.  Also, would be nice if Apple could add 2 more 'tap' functions where you could adjust the volume and tap a previous tune.  In other words instead of 3 functions, offer 5. (Pause/Play, Next, Volume & Previous). Other than that, I love them!  (I bought 'em for my wife after I had mine for a few weeks).

Title: Good quality, but not worth the money
Review_Body:
I purchased these to use for live Zoom classes online. While the sound output quality is reasonable, the microphone quality is substandard. One of my students told me I sounded like I was teaching from under a blanket. :(

For what I paid for these I expected better. I purchased so that I would have freedom of movement while teaching, and they serve that purpose, but I had hoped for better quality. Apple products have never let me down in the past, and I've been an Apple user for 20 years. This was a first.

Afterthought - Apple's earbuds have never stayed put in my ears, but these new AirPods do, even through significant movement. Ending my review on a high note!
